      <item>
        <title>Extract email from string using REGEX</title>
        <description>&lt;h2 id=&quot;extract-email-from-string-using-regex&quot;&gt;Extract email from string using REGEX&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The goal of this code snippet isn’t to make an email validator.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the REGEX is not steady but works for the most common cases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;line&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;Congratulation ! here is your email : mehdi-farsi@long-and_boring-company_name.com. Are you happy ?&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;email&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;line&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;sr&quot;&gt;/(\w|[\.\-])+@(\w|[\.\-])+\.[a-zA-Z]+/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can extract whatever you want by changing the Regex. :)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
